---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="about -- alexander campos" description="building things to protect how we think.">
  <article>
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      I'm Alex. 26, Locust Grove, Virginia. First-gen Guatemalan American.
      Business degree from George Mason. Self-taught engineer.
    </p>

    <p>
      During the day I work in regulated finance at Capital One.
      At night I write code. The ratio keeps shifting.
    </p>

    <p>
      At some point I noticed that language -- from a person, from a model,
      doesn't matter -- reshapes how someone sees themselves. Not metaphorically.
      Structurally. That observation became
      <a href="/projects/guardian">Guardian</a>, a desktop workspace for
      thinking alongside AI without losing the thread.
    </p>

    <p>
      The deeper problem Guardian surfaced was infrastructure. If your
      cognitive tools live on someone else's server, the loop isn't yours.
      <a href="/projects/forgeframe">ForgeFrame</a> is the fix --
      local-first intelligence infrastructure. Keep what's yours on your machine.
      <a href="https://reframed.works">Reframed</a> is the first product
      built on it: resume analysis and tailoring, live and taking payments.
    </p>

    <p>
      Before Capital One I was at Apple Federal Credit Union.
      Before that I was studying business and wondering why
      none of the interesting problems were in the textbook.
    </p>

    <p>
      You're looking at one of the things I built. This site is homecooked --
      Astro, vanilla JS, WebGL shaders, no frameworks.
      Everything is open-source and verifiable.
      If you opened the console, you already know the voice.
    </p>

    <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/notaprompt">GitHub</a> -- open source work</li>
      <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alexander-d-campos/">LinkedIn</a> -- professional history</li>
      <li><a href="https://substack.com/@alexinthefield">Substack</a> -- writing on identity modeling and system design</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="mailto:adc.acampos@gmail.com">adc.acampos@gmail.com</a>
    </p>
  </article>

  <script is:inline>
    console.log(
      '%c you are reading about someone building things to protect how we think. ',
      'color: #E8DCC8; font-family: monospace; font-size: 11px;'
    );
  </script>
</Page>
